The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Jaipur, Aug. 6 (PTI): A typist was today killed in a district court when an advocate, fiddling with a gun, accidentally pulled the trigger.           
	The gun had been handed to Pooran Singh by a client for licence renewal. Ridhkaran Jain, 69, suffered bullet wounds in the chest and was declared brought dead by a nearby hospital. A case has been filed against Singh who fled after the mishap.                  
	 Gurgaon(PTI): A Canada-based NRI girl on Wednesday alleged that the driver of a taxi, in which she was travelling, tried to rape her here. The 21-year-old in her police complaint said she was on the way back from a pub early on August 1 when Monu attempted to rape her, but she escaped.                  
	 About a dozen Naxalites, including four women, barged into the house of a trader in Chikmagalur district on Tuesday night and decamped with Rs 27,000 and a gun. Police said the attack may have been prompted by the trader falling out with the group .                  
	 A gangster, allegedly involved in several cases of murder and abduction in Uttar Pradesh, was killed in a police encounter on Tuesday on Sikera Link road. Rizwan was shot in a gunbattle between his gang and the police.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The family of a travel agency employee, who was killed while crossing the road, has been awarded a compensation of Rs 22 lakh by a Delhi court. Surender Singh was knocked down by a speeding car in Mahipalpur area of south Delhi in 2002.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): Four persons were injured when the roof of a platform of Govandi railway station caved in during repairs. A Central Railway spokesperson said labourers were placing new concrete shades when a beam broke, triggering the collapse.          An accident was averted as an approaching train was stopped soon after.                                                                                                                         
